<br>
Here's how your typical ubermob encounter goes. Buff for 30+ minutes, go over strategy, charge for 5 minutes of exhiliration. If you win, go to the next ubermob and start over, if you lose..... oh if you lose. If you lose you get to spend 30+ minutes rebuffing for the same mob.  And if you lose again.... oh lord.  Last night we went 3 tries on a certain big nasty and lost all three times. However, it wasn't the losing that bothered me, it was the huge boring downtime in between.  Charge blah blah Enaak dies second tank dies Mob starts outregenning our damage ouput, abort. Rez up, rebuff. Tweak tactics, blah blah Enaak dead secondary tank dead die. Rez up, rebuff. The fun part is the charge, when you get a shot at finally smacking the mofacka. However, for every 5 minutes of enjoyment, you have 30-45 minutes of inane boredom due to rebuffing. It sucks....<br>
<br>
The question is what can we do about it. First off, we can recruit more shamans so focus doesn't take 40 minutes to do. However, I hate recruiting people more for their class than who they are, although I know at times that may be neccessary. Secondly, we could just not lose. Then you have the first buff period and then the celebration and you move on to the next one. We've been working on this, but it only seems to work on stuff we know we should kill, this really tough stuff doesn't want to die first try :P.  Thirdly, and and something that I feel is farfetched but would help immensely, is the /groupbuff command. For example, if you type /groupbuff 8 it would cast the #8 spell on each member of your group in succession. Then people could just go from group to group and buff everyone up real quick. Also(and this is something I know shamans/clerics/chanters love) you could cut casting time in half if there is not an agro mob on you or your target. That would significantly lessen buffing time and hopefully speed up the long, tedious process of preparing for epic type fights. Input?<br>
<br>
Gilg<br>
<br>
